  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Geometry-TransitionCurve</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_">Transition-Curve</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">The PSMotion Transition-Curve<text style="font-size:7pt; vertical-align:super;">©</text> is used to completely eliminate Polygonal Action - also referred to as Chordal Action - as a Chain moves between two Sprockets. </para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">The geometry of chain-links and sprockets mean that the chain lifts and falls. Also, the chain-links have a linear velocity variation as each link moves onto a sprocket.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Polygonal-Action increases as the number-of-teeth in the sprockets decrease.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Polygonal-Action creates two(2) problems</para>
    <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Velocity Variation in the Chain</li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Body Text Howindent4bullets">In the general case, if a Driving Sprocket is rotating at constant speed, the chain does not move at Constant Velocity. </para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text Howindent4bullets">The peak to peak velocity variation increases as you reduce the number of teeth on the drive sprocket. Most usually, it is &#160;recommended that you use more than 17 teeth. </para>
    <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Tension Variation in the Chain.</li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Body Text Howindent4bullets">As a chain link engages with a tooth, the chain accelerates, and thus there is a tension variation.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text Howindent4bullets">Also, the pitch of the chain link is not constant </para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="Standard" rowcount="4" colcount="3">
